Police say bomb experts were promptly deployed to Yare Plaza on Thursday, September 23. [File, Standard]  Bomb experts have been deployed to Yare Plaza in Eastleigh, Nairobi, after unknown people left a note in one of its lifts warning there was an explosive in the building.  According to Starehe Sub-County Police Commander Julius Kiragu, a search for the explosive is on.  The note stated that the bomb was programmed to go off anytime from 1pm.  More to follow…  Man held over terrorism link to remain in custody  Fishermen find bomb in Lake Victoria  Bomb blast victims wait for justice, 23 years later  Remembering the 1998 US embassy bombings [PHOTOS]   23-year-old woman, Hafsa Mohamed, who went missing in Eastleigh has been rescued by police in Kayole  Hafsa Aokolewa: Msichana aliyekuwa ametekwa nyara Eastleigh amepatikana Kayole  Suspected Suicide bomber sucked out of a plane  By Kamore Maina | 1 hour ago By Betty Njeru | 13 hours ago By Collins Kweyu | 1 day ago By Jacob Ng'etich | 2 days ago